parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic shoulder belt retraction can cause the belt to overtighten, making it difficult or impossible to breathe, or fail to release, trapping the occupant. This can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The automatic shoulder belt fails to retract
overtightens
or does not release
causing discomfort or pain to the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized belt can cause the belt to fail to engage or disengage, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The motorized belt fails to engage or disengage
causing the belt to stick or not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the belt to fail to latch or unlatch, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks or fails to latch or unlatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual seat belt can cause the belt to fail to lock or latch, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The manual seat belt fails to lock or latch.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Incomplete or Intermittent Seat Belt Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete or intermittent activation of the seat belt can cause the belt to fail to secure the occupant properly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt activates incompletely or intermittently
causing the belt to stop securing the occupant while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Leading to Stalling or Engine Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies out while driving
the engine loses power
the engine catches fire
the vehicle becomes sluggish
the engine is noisy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Structural defects in engine cylinders can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine loses compression
the engine cylinder cracks
the vehicle stalls or dies out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The timing belt fails
the engine is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty cylinder head design can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The cylinder heads need to be replaced
the engine is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Crankshaft failure can cause the vehicle to become sluggish, noisy, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The crankshaft fails
the vehicle becomes sluggish
the engine is noisy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU can cause the vehicle to stall, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the vehicle is difficult or impossible to start
the vehicle experiences intermittent starting issues
the vehicle lacks a warning indicator to notify the driver of failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to serious safety risks and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The wiring harness behind the headlight catches fire
the vehicle experiences electrical system malfunctions.
